aging and accessible style, So Clean will appeal to academics and students working in business, social, cultural and imperial history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aIndustrialistsxBiographyxGreat Britain. 0aIndustrialistszGreat BritainvBiography. 0aPhilanthropistsxBiographyxGreat Britain. 0aPhilanthropistszGreat BritainvBiography. 0aSoap tradexGreat BritainxGreat Britain. 0aSoap tradezGreat Britain. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / General.2bisacsh  aAmerica.  aAustralia.  aCanada.  aGarden City movement.  aGermany.  aNapoleon.  aSunlight Soap empire.  aSwitzerland.  aWilliam Hesketh Lever.  aadvertising.  acolonial encounters.  afactory paternalism.  atown planning.1 aLewis, Brian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526130433423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526130433/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles